From bfaff941138f6c587e5bab89a48b620a03159742 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: DOSKUTSU NXEngine Port <services.claude@accounts.ecliptik.com>
Date: Fri, 24 Apr 2026 17:45:54 -0700
Subject: [PATCH 10/12] [DOSKUTSU] SDL3 mechanical renames: bulk
 renderer/surface/cursor/joystick
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Why DOS needs this: NXEngine-evo's SDL2 API surface doesn't compile against
SDL3 headers as-is. The doskutsu DOS port (Path B per project plan) targets
SDL3 directly so it can use the SDL3 DOS backend — sdl2-compat is structurally
incompatible with static-only DJGPP linkage. This is the bulk-rename slice
of the SDL2->SDL3 migration; subsequent patches handle event-enum renames
(0011), renderer-properties API (0012), audio refactor (0013-0017), and
SDL3_image swap (0018).

Per patches/nxengine-evo/README.md, this patch covers bulk-renames that are
"uniform sed-bait." Sites + signature notes:

- src/graphics/Renderer.cpp
  * SDL_FreeSurface (3) -> SDL_DestroySurface
  * SDL_CreateRGBSurfaceFrom (icon) -> SDL_CreateSurfaceFrom
    (mask layout maps to SDL_PIXELFORMAT_RGBA32 endian-neutral alias)
  * SDL_CreateRGBSurface (screenshot) -> SDL_CreateSurface
  * SDL_RenderCopy (3) -> SDL_RenderTexture (SDL_FRect via SDL_RectToFRect)
  * SDL_RenderCopyEx -> SDL_RenderTextureRotated (SDL_FRect)
  * SDL_RenderDrawLine -> SDL_RenderLine (float coords)
  * SDL_RenderFillRect/SDL_RenderFillRects: now take SDL_FRect
  * SDL_ShowCursor signature change: bool toggle gone; pair with SDL_HideCursor
  * SDL_SetWindowFullscreen takes bool (not flags)
  * SDL_CreateWindow signature change: position params dropped; followed by
    SDL_SetWindowPosition
  * SDL_CreateRenderer signature change: (window, name) only; flags gone.
    Passing NULL for now; the SDL_RENDERER_SOFTWARE force lives in 0004.
  * SDL_WINDOW_SHOWN removed (windows shown by default); test !HIDDEN
  * SDL_GetWindowFlags returns SDL_WindowFlags (Uint64)
  * SDL_GetWindowDisplayIndex -> SDL_GetDisplayForWindow (SDL_DisplayID)
  * SDL_GetDesktopDisplayMode now returns const SDL_DisplayMode* (no out-param)
  * SDL_RenderGetViewport -> SDL_GetRenderViewport
  * SDL_RenderReadPixels: returns SDL_Surface* directly
  NOTE: SDL_RendererInfo + SDL_GetRendererInfo are deliberately untouched here
  and migrated separately in 0012-sdl3-renderer-properties.patch (the brief
  splits that out as a "genuinely different API surface" concern).

- src/graphics/Font.cpp
  * SDL_FreeSurface -> SDL_DestroySurface
  * SDL_RenderCopy (4) -> SDL_RenderTexture (SDL_FRect via SDL_RectToFRect)

- src/graphics/Surface.cpp
  * SDL_FreeSurface (2) -> SDL_DestroySurface
  * SDL_SetColorKey -> SDL_SetSurfaceColorKey (with bool, not SDL_TRUE)
  * SDL_MapRGB -> SDL_MapSurfaceRGB (no surface->format dereference needed)

- src/graphics/zoom.cpp
  * SDL_GetColorKey -> SDL_GetSurfaceColorKey
  * SDL_FreeSurface (3) -> SDL_DestroySurface
  * SDL_CreateRGBSurface (3) -> SDL_CreateSurface (RGBA32 / source format / INDEX8)
  * surface->format->BitsPerPixel -> SDL_BITSPERPIXEL(surface->format)
    (surface->format is now an SDL_PixelFormat enum, not a struct ptr)
  * surface->format->palette -> SDL_GetSurfacePalette(surface)
    (palette no longer hung off format)

- src/graphics/pngfuncs.cpp
  * SDL_CreateRGBSurface -> SDL_CreateSurface (SDL_PIXELFORMAT_ARGB8888)

- src/input.cpp (joystick API only — event-enum renames are 0011)
  * SDL_NumJoysticks -> SDL_GetJoysticks (instance-id list)
  * SDL_JoystickOpen(0) -> SDL_OpenJoystick(instance_id)
  * SDL_JoystickNameForIndex -> SDL_GetJoystickNameForID
  * SDL_JoystickNum{Axes,Buttons,Balls} -> SDL_GetNumJoystick{Axes,Buttons,Balls}
  * SDL_JoystickRumble -> SDL_RumbleJoystick
  * SDL_JoystickGetAxis -> SDL_GetJoystickAxis
  * SDL_JoystickGetAttached -> SDL_JoystickConnected
  * SDL_JoystickClose -> SDL_CloseJoystick

- src/slope.cpp
  * SDL_FillRect -> SDL_FillSurfaceRect
  * SDL_MapRGB -> SDL_MapSurfaceRGB

- src/trig.cpp
  * SDL_WarpMouse -> SDL_WarpMouseInWindow(NULL, ...)

- src/main.cpp
  * SDL_Init now returns bool; old `< 0` check would always be false (silent
    init failure under SDL3). Changed to `if (!SDL_Init(...))`.

- src/ResourceManager.cpp
  * SDL_GetBasePath now returns const char* owned by SDL — must NOT SDL_free.
    Removed the SDL_free; declared the local as const char*.

After this patch lands, NXEngine-evo will not yet compile against SDL3 alone:
0011 (event-enum renames) and 0012 (renderer-properties) are required for
the renderer/event subsystems to build. The patches are designed to apply as
a 0010-0012 cluster; the split is for review readability and bisect
granularity within the SDL3 migration block.
